## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of low-level synchronization primitives, cache-line considerations, and safe reuse of barriers in multi-threaded code.

## Key Concepts

- Sense-reversing barrier pattern
- Cache-line padding to avoid false sharing
- Atomic operations and memory_order semantics

## Code Example

```c
// barrier_init
void barrier_init(barrier_t *b, int n) { b->n = n; b->count = 0; b->sense = false; }

// barrier_wait
void barrier_wait(barrier_t *b, bool *local) {
    bool local_sense = !*local;
    if (atomic_fetch_add(&b->count, 1) == b->n - 1) {
        atomic_store(&b->count, 0);
        atomic_store(&b->sense, local_sense);
    } else {
        while (atomic_load(&b->sense) != local_sense) pause();
    }
    *local = local_sense;
}
```

