## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of basic memory management without dynamic allocation, a common pattern in low-latency systems.

## Key Concepts

- Fixed-size pool basics
- Free-list within block memory
- Alignment and safety checks
- Simple double-free detection (debug)

## Code Example

```c
#define BLOCK_SIZE 64
#define N_BLOCKS 1024
typedef struct Block { struct Block* next; unsigned char payload[BLOCK_SIZE - sizeof(struct Block*)]; } Block;
static Block blocks[N_BLOCKS];
static Block* free_list;

void pool_init(void){
  for(int i=0;i<N_BLOCKS-1;i++) blocks[i].next = &blocks[i+1];
  blocks[N_BLOCKS-1].next = NULL;
  free_list = &blocks[0];
}
void* pool_alloc(void){
  if(!free_list) return NULL;
  Block* b = free_list;
  free_list = b->next;
  return (void*)b->payload;
}
void pool_free(void* p){
  Block* b = (Block*)((char*)p - offsetof(Block, payload));
  b->next = free_list;
  free_list = b;
}
```

