## Why This Is Asked
Tests practical low-level synchronization and memory-order reasoning.

## Key Concepts
- Ticket-based spinlock yields FIFO fairness
- Atomics: fetch_add, load, store
- Memory orders: acquire on lock, release on unlock, relaxed during waiting

## Code Example
```c
typedef struct {
  _Atomic uint32_t next;
  _Atomic uint32_t serve;
} TicketLock;
void init(TicketLock* t){ atomic_store(&t->next,0); atomic_store(&t->serve,0); }
uint32_t lock(TicketLock* t){ uint32_t my = atomic_fetch_add(&t->next,1); while (atomic_load(&t->serve) != my) { _mm_pause(); } return my; }
void unlock(TicketLock* t, uint32_t my){ atomic_store_explicit(&t->serve, my+1, memory_order_release); }
```

