## Allocation Path (Pseudo-code)

```c
void* allocate(size_t size) {
    int idx = size_to_index(size);
    PerThreadCache* tc = get_thread_cache();

    if (tc->counts[idx] > 0) {
        tc->counts[idx]--;
        return tc->pools[idx];
    }
    // Cache miss: refill from global pool
    return refill_and_allocate(tc, idx);
}

void* refill_and_allocate(PerThreadCache* tc, int idx) {
    Block* batch = global_pool_extract(BATCH_SIZE);
    if (batch == NULL) return NULL;

    // Push remaining to thread cache
    tc->pools[idx] = batch->next;
    tc->counts[idx] = BATCH_SIZE - 1;
    return batch;
}
```

## Deallocation Path (Pseudo-code)

```c
void deallocate(void* ptr, size_t size) {
    int idx = size_to_index(size);
    PerThreadCache* tc = get_thread_cache();

    Block* block = (Block*)ptr;

    if (tc->counts[idx] < CACHE_CAPACITY) {
        block->next = tc->pools[idx];
        tc->pools[idx] = block;
        tc->counts[idx]++;
    } else {
        // Cache full: return excess to global pool
        return_excess_to_pool(tc, idx);
        block->next = tc->pools[idx];
        tc->pools[idx] = block;
        tc->counts[idx] = 1;
    }
}
```

## Avoiding Cross-Core Cache Thrashing

1. **False sharing prevention**: Each per-thread cache is aligned to a full cache line (64 bytes), ensuring updates from different threads do not share the same cache line
