- **In-block free list**: Stores next-pointer directly within each free block, using only 8 bytes per block
- **O(1) operations**: Both allocate and free simply manipulate a head pointer—no traversal required
- **8-byte alignment**: Block size is naturally aligned; allocator returns properly aligned addresses
