## Lockless Cross-Thread Config Exchange Design

### Data Structures

```c
#define BUFFER_SIZE 64

typedef struct {
    uint8_t data[BUFFER_SIZE];
    uint32_t crc;
} ConfigBuffer;

typedef struct {
    ConfigBuffer buffers[2];
    _Atomic uint64_t version;  // Even = buffer[0] valid, Odd = buffer[1] valid
} ConfigExchange;
```

### Writer (Producer)

```c
void writer_update(ConfigExchange* cx, const uint8_t* new_config, size_t len) {
    // Determine which buffer to write to (toggle between 0 and 1)
    uint64_t current_version = atomic_load_acquire(&cx->version);
    uint64_t next_idx = current_version & 1;  // 0 or 1 based on parity

    // Write new config to the "next" buffer
    memcpy(cx->buffers[next_idx].data, new_config, len);
    cx->buffers[next_idx].crc = crc32(cx->buffers[next_idx].data, len);

    // Publish: increment version (toggle parity) with release semantics
    atomic_store_release(&cx->version, current_version + 1);
}
```

### Reader (Consumer)

```c
bool reader_read(ConfigExchange* cx, uint8_t* local_copy) {
    uint64_t version1;
    ConfigBuffer* buf;

    do {
        // Acquire the current version
        version1 = atomic_load_acquire(&cx->version);

        // Ensure version is even (valid state)
        if (version1 & 1) return false;

        buf = &cx->buffers[version1 & 1];  // Select buffer based on version

        // Copy to local memory
        memcpy(local_copy, buf->data, BUFFER_SIZE);
        uint32_t local_crc = crc32(local_copy, BUFFER_SIZE);

        // Re-check version (acquire barrier)
        uint64_t version2 = atomic_load_acquire(&cx->version);

        // Accept only if unchanged and even
    } while (version1 != version2 || (version2 & 1));

    // Verify CRC
    return (local_crc == buf->crc);
}
```

### Basic Test Plan

| Test Case | Description | Expected Result |
|-----------|-------------|------------------|
| **Single Thread Write/Read** | Writer writes values, reader reads them | Reader receives correct data with valid CRC |
| **Concurrent Access** | Writer continuously updates while reader reads | No data races, CRC always valid |
| **Torn Read Detection** | Writer updates mid-read | Reader detects version mismatch, retries |
| **Version Parity Check** | Reader encounters odd version | Reader rejects and retries |
| **CRC Corruption** | Simulate bit flip in buffer | Reader detects invalid CRC, rejects |
| **High Frequency** | Rapid writer/reader cycles (100k+) | All reads succeed, no missed updates |
| **Memory Ordering** | Run with thread sanitizer | No undefined behavior detected |

